  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "How to proceed with MICU self-assessment"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The self-diagnostic function of the MICU can be performed by checking DTC (using HDS) or DTC (not using HDS)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Self-diagnosis mode 1"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Performs self-diagnosis of MICU communication errors and indicates failure codes by the number of times the interior light blinks."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Self-diagnosis mode 2"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "By operating the input lines (switches, sensors, etc.) to each unit, the interior lights indicate whether the lines are normal or not."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Example: The"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1410_5.0_jpn_11579599_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Inspect No. A14 (10A) fuse in relay box and No. D1 (15A) fuse in sub-fuse/relay box for blown and connected conditions before performing inspection."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Turn the interior light switch to the DOOR position."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Turn ignition to ON mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Steps 3-6 are done within 10 seconds"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "",
      "text": "3. Hold the passing switch in the ON position and turn the headlight switch (small) ON."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1410_5.0_jpn_11579600_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Passing switch is turned OFF and ON and held."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Turn the headlight switch (small) OFF and repeat ON/OFF twice more."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "6",
      "text": "Turn the passing switch OFF."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "7",
      "text": "After approximately 2 seconds, the interior light blinks once and then turns off to indicate that the unit has entered self-diagnostic mode 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "DTC",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "symptoms",
            "header": true
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "1"
          },
          {
            "text": "Communication error between MICU and other units"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "5"
          },
          {
            "text": "MICU cannot receive VSP/NE frames sent from the combination meter"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Work from the mode 1 state."
        },
        {
          "text": "Steps 1-4 should be performed within 10 seconds."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "",
      "text": "1. Hold the passing switch in the ON position and turn the headlight switch (small) ON."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1410_5.0_jpn_11579601_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Passing switch is turned OFF and ON and held."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Turn the headlight switch (small) OFF and repeat ON/OFF twice more."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Turn the passing switch OFF."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "After about 2 seconds, the interior light blinks twice and then goes off, indicating that the unit has entered self-diagnostic mode 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "When shifting to self-diagnosis mode 1 again, repeat steps 1-4."
    },
